{
  "texts": [
    "MKMK, when used as a supplementary cementitious material at replacement levels of 10-15%, significantly enhances concrete durability.",
    "Ouldkhaoua et al. [71] found that MK improved resistance to chloride and gas permeability and limited expansion from alkali-silica reactions, strengthening concrete against aggressive environments.",
    "Singh and Murugan [73] reported that MK increased energy absorption and crack resistance, boosting toughness and longevity.",
    "Zhan et al. [74] noted that it reduces drying shrinkage and chloride permeability, while Jiang et al.",
    "[72] highlighted its ability to decrease porosity and enhance resistance to chloride ion penetration by refining the concrete pore structure."
  ]
}